## âœ… Practical Work

**Step 1: Install k3s (Kubernetes) on EC2**

```bash
curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | sh -
```

*Roman Urdu:* Ye command lightweight k3s cluster install karti hai. Single node dev cluster ready ho jata hai.

**Step 2: Set KUBECONFIG for kubectl**

```bash
export KUBECONFIG=/etc/rancher/k3s/k3s.yaml
```

*Roman Urdu:* Kubectl ko batata hai ke cluster ka config file kahan se load karna hai.

**Step 3: Verify Node Status**

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

*Roman Urdu:* Cluster mein node ready hai ya nahi, status check karo.

---

**Step 4: Install Helm**

```bash
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
helm version
```

*Roman Urdu:* Helm install karo aur verify karo ke sahi install hua.

**Step 5: Create First Chart**

```bash
helm create mychart
```

*Roman Urdu:* Ye command chart folder banata hai jisme `templates/`, `values.yaml`, aur `Chart.yaml` hoti hai.

**Folder Structure:**

```
mychart/
â”œâ”€â”€ Chart.yaml
â”œâ”€â”€ values.yaml
â”œâ”€â”€ templates/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ deployment.yaml
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ service.yaml
```

**Step 6: Deploy App Using Helm**

```bash
helm install myapp ./mychart
kubectl get all
helm list
```

*Roman Urdu:* Chart ke base par app deploy hoti hai. Resources aur Helm release verify karo.

---

## ðŸ“š Assignment: Deploy App Using Helm Chart

**Step 1: Modify values.yaml**

```bash
nano mychart/values.yaml
```

Update file:

```yaml
image:
  repository: nginx
  tag: latest
service:
  type: NodePort
  port: 80
```

*Roman Urdu:*

* `repository: nginx` â†’ DockerHub se nginx image use hogi
* `tag: latest` â†’ Latest version pull hoga
* `type: NodePort` â†’ Service externally expose hogi
* `port: 80` â†’ App ka internal port

Save & exit: Ctrl + O â†’ Enter â†’ Ctrl + X

**Step 2: Reinstall Helm Chart**

```bash
helm uninstall myapp
helm install myapp ./mychart
kubectl get svc
```

*Roman Urdu:* Pehle existing deployment remove karo, phir updated chart deploy karo aur service verify karo.

**Step 3: Access App in Browser**

```bash
curl http://checkip.amazonaws.com
```

Browser URL: `http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:<NodePort>`
*Roman Urdu:* EC2 ka public IP aur NodePort use karke browser mein open karo. Nginx welcome page dikhega.

**Important:** Agar browser se access nahi ho raha, to EC2 security group mein NodePort range 30000â€“32667 allow honi chahiye.

